post_content:
&nbsp;

My Ad dream began years ago when I walked into Grey for a V.O. Audition. My Spidey Sense told me that I belonged on the other side of that booth. I have been working towards that dream ever since. There has been traffic; children, my husband’s baseball career, and a family of wiener dogs. But I’m here now. I’m hungry and humble. I am ready to be a part of a creative team that delivers brilliance, in 30-second increments.

I'm a recent grad of Denver Ad School. Prior to DAD, I spent my days teaching Pilates and my nights on a professional theatre stage.  A “yes and” mentality, adaptability, innovation, and problem-solving, are just a few of the skills I have been able to take with me in my work in advertising.

I dance through life.  I am very grateful for my experiences, knowledge, and friendships. I look forward to throwing all of that I have into a beautiful deep-dish creative pie.

&nbsp;

